wbqc-potentialissues-long:
Title for the icon shown on statements with non-mandatory constraint violations, usually displayed by the browser when the user hovers over the icon with the mouse cursor.
{{Related|wbqc-potentialissues-short}}
{{Related|wbqc-issues-long}}

wbqc-suggestions-long:
Title for the icon shown on statements with suggestion constraint violations, usually displayed by the browser when the user hovers over the icon with the mouse cursor.
{{Related|wbqc-suggestions-short}}
{{Related|wbqc-issues-long}}

wbqc-cached-days:
Message informing the user that a constraint check result might be outdated by up to ''n'' days.
{{Related|wbqc-cached-minutes}}
{{Related|wbqc-cached-generic}}

wbqc-violation-message-no-qualifiers:
Message for a violation of the “Qualifiers” constraint, when a statement has a qualifier but the property has no permitted qualifiers. This is a special case of {{msg-mw|wbqc-violation-message-qualifiers}}. Parameters:
* $1 is the qualifier property that is not permitted.
{{Related|wbqc-violation-message-qualifiers}}

wbqc-violation-message-range-time-leftop:
Message for a violation of the “Range” constraint, when the value of a statement is later than allowed (for a time range with no lower limit and the current day as the upper limit). Parameters:
* $1 is the property of the statement.
* $2 is the value of the statement.
{{Related|wbqc-violation-message-range-time-leftopen}}
{{Related|wbqc-violation-message-range-time-rightopen-leftnow}}

wbqc-violation-message-range-time-righto:
Message for a violation of the “Range” constraint, when the value of a statement is earlier than allowed (for a time range with no upper limit and the current day as the lower limit). Parameters:
* $1 is the property of the statement.
* $2 is the value of the statement.
{{Related|wbqc-violation-message-range-time-rightopen}}
{{Related|wbqc-violation-message-range-time-leftopen-rightnow}}

wbqc-violation-message-units-none:
Message for a violation of the “allowed units” constraint, when a property should not be used with any units but the value has a unit. Parameters:
* $1 is the property ID of the property to which the constraint applies.
{{Related|Wbqc-violation-message-units-none}}
